<div id="review_4246550053" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4246550053" />
    <a title="lina" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/140256349-lina"><img alt="lina" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1634867644p2/140256349.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4246550053?book_show_action=true">Nov 24, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="lina" class="user" itemprop="url" name="lina" href="/user/show/140256349-lina">lina</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9788408083497" href="/book/show/14290904-los-renglones-torcidos-de-dios">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4246550053" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17327784461642512235">i wanted to adore this book, i really did. i loved the plot. i loved the way the writer really messed up with my head trying to figure out which truth was the real truth. but there where a couple of things that made me not give this a 5 star review. thinking about it and truly digesting the story, they are all things that nurture the story and makes us understand the true background of it all. <br/><br/>the protagonist is sooooo annoying, her superiority complex is entertaining but only for the first 100 </span>
  <span id="freeText17327784461642512235" style="display:none">i wanted to adore this book, i really did. i loved the plot. i loved the way the writer really messed up with my head trying to figure out which truth was the real truth. but there where a couple of things that made me not give this a 5 star review. thinking about it and truly digesting the story, they are all things that nurture the story and makes us understand the true background of it all. <br /><br />the protagonist is sooooo annoying, her superiority complex is entertaining but only for the first 100 pages. the way she charms everyone she meets is just so unrealistic. she's a narcisist and has a <br />messianic complex that left me wth-ing. then i remembered this book is from 1979, with all the patriarchal references of women written by a man, and the stereotypes that existed back then on mental illnesses.<br /><br />also, it was sooooo long. it literally took me 2 months to read it (both because i didn't have much time to read, and also because the book is so dense). it vomits descriptions that a couple pages later you have already forgotten, a bunch of characters that you end up mixing up, and confusing dialogues that were completely unnecessary.<br /><br />all in all, this is a great book, but i feel like it could have delivered the same impression in 250-ish pages rather than 430-ish pages. the writer does an amazing job in tricking you to believe one side of the story until the very end, it left an impact, but i don't think i would ever read it again. the 4 stars review instead of 3 is just for courtesy, as i recognize this is an old book that was something new during its time.<br /><br />now i'm gonna read a light hearted novel or something to give my brain a break from all the processing this book made me do.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17327784461642512235" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

