<div id="review_34448767" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/34448767" />
    <a title="Lausº" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1588424-laus"><img alt="Lausº" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1518800642p2/1588424.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/34448767?book_show_action=true">Oct 03, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lausº" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lausº" href="/user/show/1588424-laus">Lausº</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9788432053986" href="/book/show/67009.Los_renglones_torcidos_de_Dios">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer34448767" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1025674040151073919">The title refers to a respectful manner in which the author called the mentally ill in an asylum. <br/>The novel is about a woman who was admitted to the clinic to solve a crime ... but as it progresses the story makes you doubt whether it is she really who she say to be or if everything is part of her mental illness. Its a very smart way to portray that we all have some madness and that no line is completely straight.<br/> ---------------------------------ESPAÑOL-----------------------------------<br/>El títu</span>
  <span id="freeText1025674040151073919" style="display:none">The title refers to a respectful manner in which the author called the mentally ill in an asylum. <br />The novel is about a woman who was admitted to the clinic to solve a crime ... but as it progresses the story makes you doubt whether it is she really who she say to be or if everything is part of her mental illness. Its a very smart way to portray that we all have some madness and that no line is completely straight.<br /> ---------------------------------ESPAÑOL-----------------------------------<br />El título hace referencia a una forma respetuosa en que el autor denomina a los enfermos mentales de un manicomio. <br />La novela se desarrolla alrededor de una mujer que ingresa a la clínica para resolver un crimen... pero conforme avanza la historia la narración te hace dudar sobre si realmente es quien dice ser o si todo es parte de su enfermedad. Una manera muy inteligente de retratar que todos tenemos algo de locos y que ningún renglón es completamente recto.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1025674040151073919" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


